                                         CAPE TOWN - Those planning to party hard this silly season, beware of a cardiac complication known as “holiday heart syndrome”. Typically characterised by severe heart palpitations, the condition is caused by heavy alcohol consumption. Experts say large quantities of, among others, brandy, gin, vodka and wine are the biggest culprits. They suggest staying hydrated in water and avoiding caffeinated drinks to help your heart survive the festive season cheers.